" ```json\n{\n  \"title\": \"Hard Python Coding Question\",\n  \"description\": \"Given a list of integers, find the longest subarray where the absolute difference between any two elements is at most 1. Write a function `longest_subarray` that takes a list of integers and returns the length of this longest subarray.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef longest_subarray(nums: List[int]) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `nums` (List[int]): A list of integers.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the length of the longest subarray where the absolute difference between any two elements is at most 1.\",\n  \"code\": \"from typing import List\\n\\ndef longest_subarray(nums: List[int]) -> int:\\n    if not nums: return 0\\n    max_length = 1\\n    dp = [1] * len(nums)\\n    for i in range(1, len(nums)):\\n        for j in range(i):\\n            if abs(nums[i] - nums[j]) <= 1 and dp[j] + 1 > dp[i]:\\n                dp[i] = dp[j] + 1\\n        max_length = max(max_length, dp[i])\\n    return max_length\\n\",\n  \"tests\": [\n    \"assert longest_subarray([10, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5]) == 4\",\n    \"assert longest_subarray([8, 7, 6, 5, 4, 3]) == 1\",\n    \"assert longest_subarray([1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9]) == 9\",\n    \"assert longest_subarray([10, 1, 2, 2, 3, 3, 4, 4, 5]) == 5\"\n  ]\n}\n```"